<h2 id="introduction">1. Introduction:</h2>
<p>The Data Governance Platform developed by 10Pearls Organization is a robust solution designed to facilitate effective management, protection, and utilization of enterprise data assets. This platform enables organizations to establish data governance policies, ensure regulatory compliance, and improve data quality and security across the data lifecycle.</p>
<h2 id="system-requirements">2. System Requirements:</h2>
<h3 id="hardware-requirements">Hardware Requirements:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Processor: Intel Xeon or equivalent</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>RAM: 16GB or higher</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Storage: 200GB free disk space</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Network: Gigabit Ethernet</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="software-requirements">Software Requirements:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Operating System: Linux (Ubuntu 18.04 LTS recommended)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Database: PostgreSQL 11+</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Web Server: Apache Tomcat 9+</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Java Development Kit (JDK): Version 11+</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="installation">3. Installation:</h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Install PostgreSQL database server on the target system.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Set up Apache Tomcat as the web server for hosting the Data Governance Platform.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Clone the Data Governance Platform repository from the official 10Pearls GitHub repository.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Configure database settings and initialize the database schema using provided scripts.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Deploy the platform WAR file to the Apache Tomcat webapps directory.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Start the Apache Tomcat server and verify successful deployment by accessing the platform URL.</p>
</li>
</ol>
